<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>FormErrors decorator expects $form-&gt;getMessages() to return array containing element's and subforms' names as keys, but if $form-&gt;setIsArray(true), topmost key will contain form's name. 
Next, decorator will request element with that name (form name) from the form, which is obviously can't be there.
Finally nothing is rendered.</p>

